# What goes to GitHub: the reproducible skeleton — build_baseline.py, the README,
# per-run meta.yaml, the final ATE/RTE table, and the two recorded WMR timing
# inputs (display.csv + camera.csv). Everything else is large and regenerable by
# `python3 runs/build_baseline.py`: the basalt intermediates (slam/), the GT
# copies (baseline_targets/), the estimate trajectories (baseline_eval/), and
# each WMR run's own discarded SLAM outputs (filtering/prediction/imu/...).

# heavy / regenerable by default
*.csv
*.png
out/
plots/

# regenerable working trees — never push
baseline_eval/
baseline_targets/
slam/

# keep docs + per-run metadata + template + the final table
!README.md
!_template/
!**/meta.yaml
!baseline_table.txt
!baseline_table.json

# keep ONLY the recorded WMR timing inputs (the actual recorded "datasets").
# Force-add a run's other CSVs with `git add -f runs/NN_label/<file>` if needed.
!**/display.csv
!**/camera.csv
